*Ingredients*
For 4 servings

1kg potatoes
600g broccoli
100g vegan margarine
250 ml soy cooking cream
        Salt
        pepper
1 teaspoon paprika powder
0.5 tsp oregano
0.5 tsp thyme
0.5 tsp rosemary
1 clove of garlic
3 tbsp wheat flour type 405
250 ml vegetable broth
6 tbsp yeast flakes

--------------------------------
*Preparation*


Step 1 
Peel the potatoes and cut them into small cubes. Wash the broccoli, separate the florets and blanch for about 2 minutes. 
Preheat oven to 180Â°C. Grease the baking dish with 1 teaspoon of the margarine.

Step 2 
Mix the soy cooking cream with salt, pepper, paprika powder, oregano, thyme and rosemary. 
Peel the garlic, press it and add it. Mix the potatoes and broccoli with the cream and spread it in the tin.

Step 3 
Heat the remaining margarine in a saucepan. Sweat the flour in it. 
Pour in vegetable broth and stir in the yeast flakes. Bring to the boil and simmer for about 2 minutes while stirring.

Step 4
Season with pepper and pour over potatoes and broccoli. Bake until golden brown in about 45-55 minutes.
